title: The votes of the Honourable House of Commons, in vindication of the eleven members charged by the army.
author: England and Wales. Parliament. House of Commons.
notes: Dated: Die Veneris 25 Junii, 1647. Signed: Hen. Elsynge Cler. Parl. Dom. Com.

After debate on the demand of the army for suspending Denzill Hollis, Sir Philip Stapleton, Sir William Lewis, Sir John Clotworthy, Sir William Waller, Sir John Maynard, Maj.-Gen. Massy, Mr. Glyn, Recorder of London, Col. Walter Long, Col. Edward Harley, and Anthony Nicoll, before any particular charge against them is made: -- Cf. Steele.
